
1.  Security & User Management (Highest Priority)
Password Hashing: Currently, passwords are saved in plain text. Update the 

register
 and 

login_view
 in 

views.py
 to use Django's make_password and check_password.
Access Control: Use the @login_required decorator on the 

dashboard
, 

manage_teacher
, and 

save_teacher
 views to prevent unauthorized URL access.
Django Admin Integration: Register the 

Teacher
 and 

Users
 models in 

admin.py
 to leverage Django’s built-in, secure administrative interface.
2.  Data Visualization & Analytics
Since your 

requirements.txt
 already includes Plotly, Dash, and Pandas, you can add a "Statistics" tab:

Teacher Distribution: Create a pie chart showing teachers per subject.
Qualification Overview: A bar chart visualizing staff experience/qualification levels.
Leave Analytics: Use Pandas to calculate average leave days per month and display it on the dashboard.
3.  Enhanced Teacher Profiles
File Uploads (Photos/CVs): Add an ImageField or FileField to the 

Teacher
 model to store profile pictures or resume documents (requires Pillow, which is already in your requirements).
Status Tracking: Add a Status field (e.g., Active, On Leave, Resigned) to filter the teacher directory effectively.
Subject Mapping: Instead of a simple text field for subject, create a separate Subject model to handle teachers who handle multiple subjects.
4.  Productivity Tools
Global Search & Filter: Add a search bar to the 

manage_teacher.html
 page to filter by name or subject instantly.
Export to CSV/PDF: Implement a "Download Report" button that uses Python's csv module or ReportLab to generate staff lists for printing.
Bulk Import: A feature to upload an Excel/CSV file to add multiple teachers at once (highly useful for initial setup).
5.  UI/UX Modernization
Frontend Framework: Swap the custom 

style.css
 for Bootstrap 5 or Tailwind CSS to make the system fully responsive for mobile/tablet use.
Modals for CRUD: Instead of redirecting to a separate 

edit_teacher.html
 page, use Bootstrap Modals to edit teacher info without leaving the main table.
Toast Notifications: Add "Success" or "Error" pop-up messages when a record is saved or deleted to improve user feedback.
6.  Deployment & Robustness
Environment Variables: Move sensitive settings (like SECRET_KEY) from settings.py to a .env file since you are targeting deployment on Render.
Form Validation: Use Django Forms or ModelForms instead of manual request.POST parsing to handle data validation and error messaging more elegantly.